# Docker (ФК «Фаворит»)

## Stack

| Service | Container | Port | Purpose |
|---------|-----------|------|---------|
| PostgreSQL 16 | `favorit-postgres` | 5432 | **Primary** Prisma database (required) |
| Redis 7 | `favorit-redis` | 6379 | Cache (reserved) |
| MinIO | `favorit-minio` | 9000, 9001 | S3-compatible file storage |

Compose file: `docker/docker-compose.yml`

## Commands

```bash
bash scripts/docker-up.sh      # smart start (skips Postgres if :5432 busy)
bash scripts/docker-check.sh   # status
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml down
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml logs -f minio
```

Root `package.json`: `pnpm docker:up`, `pnpm docker:check`, `pnpm docker:down`

## Environment

After `docker:up`, enable uploads:

```env
S3_ENABLED="true"
S3_ENDPOINT="http://localhost:9000"
S3_BUCKET="favorit-media"
```

Restart API after changing `.env`.

MinIO console: http://localhost:9001 (`minioadmin` / `minioadmin`)

## Notes

- PostgreSQL runs **only in Docker** (`favorit-postgres`). If port 5432 is busy by local Postgres, run `bash scripts/migrate-to-docker-postgres.sh`.
- Never run `docker compose down -v` without explicit user approval (deletes DB volumes).
- Skill: `docker-expert` for advanced container work.
